                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.—Received, via Taku, August 27.
                        Date lost in transmission.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Conger reports that since his last dispatch there have been no important
                    movements. The military is endeavoring to restore order. No representative of
                    the Chinese Government encountered yet. Several ministers of the Tsungli Yamen
                    reported to be in the city, and are expected to appear soon. Two thousand
                    Germans arrived to-day. Generals believe Imperial palace practically vacant, and
                    decide not to enter it.)</p>
            </div>
